pd_0_com_0text: Silly old me? Oh, you're a sweetheart. I'm just having a wee picnic here in the garden.
pd_0_com_1text: You need me to leave? Fine, fine, nana will get a move on just for you, pumpkin.
pd_0_com_2text: You look freezing, though, are you sure you don't want a scarf?
pd_0_com_3text: Bring me some items and I'll happily knit anything you want.
pd_1_com_0text: I'm awfully parched as of late...
pd_1_com_1text: But no matter. Let me know if you need something crafted for you!
pd_2_com_0text: I see you have some items, there! I could make you a nice net to go and catch some butterflies.
pd_2_com_1text: ...Ta-da! A net, just for you, my little cherry pie.
pd_3_com_1text: My, I'm still awfully thirsty... Could you be a dear and maybe try catching some juice for me?
pd_4_com_0text: (Catch juice... with a net? Wouldn't a glass or something be more effective?)
pd_5_com_0text: Oh, a glass of juice! Aren't you a sweetheart?
pd_5_com_1text: I finally have the energy to leave, but my, what am I to do with all this leftover silk?
pd_5_com_2text: Here, my little angel, take as much as you'd like. It will keep you nice and warm. Ta-ta!
